1
00:00:20,658 --> 00:00:23,691
For weeks, rumors have
spread across Mars...

2
00:00:23,761 --> 00:00:26,096
from outposts to settlements...

3
00:00:26,161 --> 00:00:28,169
from town to town.

4
00:00:28,242 --> 00:00:32,682
Something that had been buried for
centuries has just been uncovered.

5
00:00:32,753 --> 00:00:37,063
And as this mysterious force
moves across the southern valley...

6
00:00:37,138 --> 00:00:39,625
it leaves behind only silence...

7
00:00:39,697 --> 00:00:41,388
and death.

8
00:02:28,015 --> 00:02:30,088
Take your seats, please.

9
00:02:40,335 --> 00:02:42,091
I just talked with the Cartel.

10
00:02:42,158 --> 00:02:44,069
They're concerned that the rumors
are getting out of control.

11
00:02:44,144 --> 00:02:46,892
They'd like to make a statement
in two hours.

12
00:02:46,958 --> 00:02:50,091
Some of you may not know
we've had another incident.

13
00:02:50,192 --> 00:02:52,133
At 1520 hours yesterday,
a freight train...

14
00:02:52,239 --> 00:02:54,475
Trans Marineris 74 Yankee...

15
00:02:54,542 --> 00:02:57,412
returned from the southern valley
on autopilot.

16
00:02:57,518 --> 00:02:59,973
Get to your security stations now!

17
00:03:09,550 --> 00:03:10,760
Let's move.

18
00:03:17,807 --> 00:03:20,677
Initial reports indicated
it was a ghost train.

19
00:03:20,751 --> 00:03:22,276
It appeared no one was aboard...

20
00:03:22,381 --> 00:03:25,678
until a single survivor was
discovered in the rear compartment.

21
00:03:25,774 --> 00:03:27,563
Call for a med tech backup.

22
00:03:27,631 --> 00:03:29,539
Lieutenant Melanie Ballard...

23
00:03:29,645 --> 00:03:32,612
second officer,
first squad of escort police.

24
00:03:32,686 --> 00:03:34,539
They were assigned
to transfer a prisoner...

25
00:03:34,605 --> 00:03:37,475
from the jail at Shining Canyon Mine
back here to Chryse.

26
00:03:38,734 --> 00:03:41,580
Lieutenant Ballard was taken
to hospital under guard.

27
00:03:42,286 --> 00:03:45,635
She had superficial wounds, but was
in otherwise good physical condition.

28
00:03:45,710 --> 00:03:49,451
However, traces of an illegal
substance, tetramonochloride...

29
00:03:49,517 --> 00:03:51,427
were found in her system.

30
00:03:53,357 --> 00:03:54,437
Bring her in, please.

31
00:04:06,957 --> 00:04:08,868
Lieutenant Ballard,
please be seated.

32
00:04:10,029 --> 00:04:13,324
Do I get a lawyer, or don't police
officers have rights these days?

33
00:04:13,388 --> 00:04:16,616
Representation by counsel
won't be necessary.

34
00:04:16,684 --> 00:04:19,467
Your rights are protected
by the Matronage.

35
00:04:19,533 --> 00:04:21,094
You can speak freely.

36
00:04:21,166 --> 00:04:23,718
- Then I'm not being charged?
- Sit down, Lieutenant.

37
00:04:23,789 --> 00:04:25,218
This is a discovery hearing...

38
00:04:25,293 --> 00:04:28,358
and your presence is required
as ranking officer.

39
00:04:28,460 --> 00:04:30,532
I want your after-action report.

40
00:04:30,636 --> 00:04:33,801
Where's the rest of your team,
the prisoner you picked up?

41
00:04:33,868 --> 00:04:36,169
What happened at Shining Canyon?

42
00:04:37,420 --> 00:04:41,894
Last Friday at 1750, we were
slamming through a dust storm...

43
00:04:41,964 --> 00:04:44,202
on the edge of the southern valley.

44
00:04:45,517 --> 00:04:47,272
74 Yankee was an ore hauler...

45
00:04:47,340 --> 00:04:49,510
servicing the mines
in the outer sector.

46
00:04:50,765 --> 00:04:54,212
My squad was hitching a ride
into Shining Canyon.

47
00:04:54,284 --> 00:04:55,844
You beat me.

48
00:04:56,492 --> 00:04:59,338
- Looks like you played tarts before.
- No, I've never done this.

49
00:05:00,204 --> 00:05:02,593
Let's spin 'em again.
One down and one up.

50
00:05:07,596 --> 00:05:09,255
Fuck me! The five of bats.

51
00:05:09,324 --> 00:05:11,812
You got the wheel up.
What's your wager?

52
00:05:11,885 --> 00:05:13,891
Five bucks.

53
00:05:20,140 --> 00:05:22,376
Helena? Hey.

54
00:05:22,445 --> 00:05:24,134
Sorry.

55
00:05:24,202 --> 00:05:26,822
Weather station's tracking a huge
storm across the southern sector...

56
00:05:26,892 --> 00:05:28,834
and we're right under it by now.

57
00:05:32,011 --> 00:05:34,345
- What's the mark on it?
- 3,200 kliks.

58
00:05:34,411 --> 00:05:36,516
We should be there by 1800.

59
00:05:42,186 --> 00:05:44,360
Just let me know
if you need anything.

60
00:06:34,154 --> 00:06:35,648
You high?

61
00:06:36,843 --> 00:06:38,697
Fuck, Helena, it's just clear.

62
00:06:38,762 --> 00:06:41,577
I'll be straighter than this track
long before we hit the canyon.

63
00:06:41,675 --> 00:06:45,057
You better be. This prisoner
transfer is no sleepwalk.

64
00:06:45,130 --> 00:06:48,611
- We're picking up James Williams.
- You mean "Desolation" Williams?

65
00:06:48,683 --> 00:06:51,201
Cooling his heels
in the Shining Canyon jail.

66
00:06:51,273 --> 00:06:53,249
Deep solitary.

67
00:06:53,321 --> 00:06:56,900
- What's the charge this time?
- Murder.

68
00:06:57,482 --> 00:07:00,516
The man's been up on murder three times.
He gets off every time on self-defense.

69
00:07:00,586 --> 00:07:03,401
It's different this time.
Sounds like he finally went psycho.

70
00:07:03,466 --> 00:07:06,499
Beaucoup corpses, all mutilated.

71
00:07:06,602 --> 00:07:09,830
Williams shows up at the mine
with some bizarre-ass story.

72
00:07:09,898 --> 00:07:13,672
Sends three officers to the medevac
before they locked him down.

73
00:07:13,769 --> 00:07:17,085
- You starting to see the picture?
- And all we got is you, me...

74
00:07:17,161 --> 00:07:19,202
and this new guy Jericho
and a couple of rookies?

75
00:07:19,274 --> 00:07:21,477
What do you think
of Sergeant Jericho?

76
00:07:21,545 --> 00:07:24,806
I was hoping we'd get a good,
solid woman we could count on.

77
00:07:24,875 --> 00:07:27,143
I don't know.
I guess we'll see.

78
00:07:28,265 --> 00:07:30,851
Well...

79
00:07:30,923 --> 00:07:34,117
I need you straight, Melanie.

80
00:07:35,625 --> 00:07:38,081
Don't worry about that,
Commander.

81
00:07:38,185 --> 00:07:40,159
I'm as straight as they come.

82
00:07:40,264 --> 00:07:42,152
Such a shame.

83
00:07:45,481 --> 00:07:47,172
Check on
our transfer schedule.

84
00:07:48,041 --> 00:07:50,561
Shining Canyon.

85
00:07:50,632 --> 00:07:54,660
Shining Canyon,
this is Trans Marineris 74 Yankee.

86
00:07:54,729 --> 00:07:55,973
They ready for us?

87
00:07:56,041 --> 00:07:58,758
This storm's really kicking up a mess.
I can't get through to the tower.

88
00:07:58,825 --> 00:08:00,767
Here's your coffee, Mr. McSimms.
Three sugars and two whites.

89
00:08:00,841 --> 00:08:03,230
Just the way you like it.
You want some?

90
00:08:03,305 --> 00:08:05,640
No, thanks.
How long?

91
00:08:06,953 --> 00:08:08,862
About 40.

92
00:08:08,936 --> 00:08:10,724
Shining Canyon.

93
00:08:10,824 --> 00:08:13,311
Shining Canyon, this is
Trans Marineris 74 Yankee.

94
00:08:13,417 --> 00:08:15,391
ETA, 40 minutes.

95
00:08:16,585 --> 00:08:19,618
Everybody check your equipment.
I don't want any surprises.

96
00:08:21,928 --> 00:08:24,829
Is everything all right,
Lieutenant?

97
00:08:24,903 --> 00:08:28,035
I couldn't help but notice that charming
little scene with the queen bee.

98
00:08:28,104 --> 00:08:30,591
Yeah, well, you know how
the service is, Sergeant.

99
00:08:30,663 --> 00:08:33,925
She figures if I want to make captain,
I'll have to pay the price.

100
00:08:33,993 --> 00:08:36,742
Thing is, I don't give a damn
about wearing another bar.

101
00:08:36,808 --> 00:08:38,597
It could be that.

102
00:08:38,663 --> 00:08:41,730
Or maybe she just has
good taste in women.

103
00:08:41,832 --> 00:08:44,645
Sergeant, you are
seriously out of line.

104
00:08:44,711 --> 00:08:46,654
I'd hate to spoil my record.

105
00:08:46,759 --> 00:08:51,015
All right. I know you think
you're some pretty tough hombres.

106
00:08:52,520 --> 00:08:55,487
You've had the best training.
You have the best gear.

107
00:08:55,560 --> 00:08:58,374
You probably think this is
some routine prisoner transfer.

108
00:08:58,439 --> 00:09:00,164
But that's what I want
to bang into your heads.

109
00:09:00,232 --> 00:09:02,336
There's nothing routine
about this prisoner.

110
00:09:02,406 --> 00:09:05,724
We are here to pick up
James "Desolation" Williams.

111
00:09:05,799 --> 00:09:08,483
I want you all jack-ready
and double tough.

112
00:09:30,310 --> 00:09:32,732
Officers, you can disembark here.

113
00:09:33,478 --> 00:09:34,405
What time is departure?

114
00:09:34,470 --> 00:09:36,576
We need at least half an hour
to secure our prisoner.

115
00:09:36,647 --> 00:09:38,175
We got about
a four-hour turnaround...

116
00:09:38,247 --> 00:09:41,509
and we'll be back
at this spot at about 2200.

117
00:09:41,575 --> 00:09:43,396
You can re-board any time after that.

118
00:09:43,462 --> 00:09:45,699
See if you can raise
the yard master, will ya?

119
00:09:45,798 --> 00:09:49,693
Ed? Ed, you out there?

120
00:09:49,798 --> 00:09:51,324
Rookies, use your breathers.

121
00:09:51,430 --> 00:09:54,911
We're not gonna have air like Earth
for ten more years. Let's go.

122
00:10:17,830 --> 00:10:21,212
- God, I hate this thing.
- You'll get used to it.

123
00:10:21,317 --> 00:10:24,416
Two years ago, we were still
wearing full-face breathers.

124
00:10:24,486 --> 00:10:26,525
It takes about a month to get over
the headaches out here.

125
00:10:28,326 --> 00:10:32,254
So this is Shining Canyon?
God, what a dump.

126
00:10:32,326 --> 00:10:35,196
- First time in the boonies, rookie?
- Standard layout.

127
00:10:35,270 --> 00:10:37,473
Just another shitty boomtown
like all the others.

128
00:10:37,541 --> 00:10:39,199
Seen one, you can go home.

129
00:10:39,269 --> 00:10:41,157
You're always cold,
you can't get a decent shower...

130
00:10:41,222 --> 00:10:43,937
and they don't tell you
that a one-year contract here...

131
00:10:44,005 --> 00:10:46,274
equals two years' Earth time.

132
00:10:46,341 --> 00:10:48,197
You gotta read the fine print.

133
00:10:54,693 --> 00:10:56,067
Where is everybody?

134
00:10:57,093 --> 00:10:59,940
Yeah. Friday night,
the place should be packed.

135
00:11:00,005 --> 00:11:02,874
A whole 12 hours before sun up,
and there's money to burn...

136
00:11:02,948 --> 00:11:06,265
whores to fuck
and drugs to take.

137
00:11:06,341 --> 00:11:08,316
Instead, we got a graveyard.

138
00:11:10,214 --> 00:11:13,180
Maybe they're all inside,
spending their money.

139
00:11:13,252 --> 00:11:14,878
Mel, I'll get us squared away
at the rec-fac.

140
00:11:14,948 --> 00:11:17,404
You and Sergeant Jericho
check in at the jail.

141
00:11:18,660 --> 00:11:20,733
Save some hot water for me.

142
00:11:23,813 --> 00:11:25,916
Where were you before Chryse?

143
00:11:26,019 --> 00:11:28,355
Utopia.

144
00:11:28,420 --> 00:11:30,689
It's the arse end of the universe.

145
00:11:30,756 --> 00:11:33,986
A penal camp full of
work-amnesty cutthroats.

146
00:11:34,052 --> 00:11:35,712
Sounds nasty...

147
00:11:35,781 --> 00:11:38,432
but you seem to be
holding together all right.

148
00:11:38,501 --> 00:11:40,868
What you see is nothing.

149
00:11:40,933 --> 00:11:43,354
I have numerous
hidden talents.

150
00:11:59,173 --> 00:12:00,601
Need some help with that?

151
00:12:01,251 --> 00:12:03,935
You're persistent, aren't you?

152
00:12:04,004 --> 00:12:06,556
I've changed a few minds
in my time.

153
00:12:06,627 --> 00:12:09,695
There's not many
of us breeders around.

154
00:12:09,765 --> 00:12:12,797
I'd hate to miss a chance
to give it a go.

155
00:12:12,868 --> 00:12:14,590
What do you say?

156
00:12:22,659 --> 00:12:24,666
Hello!

157
00:12:25,507 --> 00:12:27,329
Anybody here?

158
00:12:43,235 --> 00:12:45,243
Officer to front desk.

159
00:12:55,364 --> 00:12:58,014
Well, hello, Mr. Williams.

160
00:13:02,403 --> 00:13:04,574
No one seems to be about.
What do you make of it?

161
00:13:04,643 --> 00:13:05,657
I don't know.

162
00:13:05,764 --> 00:13:07,966
Do you want me to pop the lock
and ask the prisoners?

163
00:13:08,034 --> 00:13:10,685
What do you mean, pop the lock?
That's a level-eight security door.

164
00:13:11,748 --> 00:13:14,976
I've got a mystical way with
locks and mechanical objects.

165
00:13:15,043 --> 00:13:17,148
There isn't a machine on Mars
that doesn't love me.

166
00:13:18,114 --> 00:13:20,667
How about we check with
the commander first?

167
00:13:24,225 --> 00:13:27,871
So what do you do for fun then?
Are you a gambler?

168
00:13:27,939 --> 00:13:32,346
No. I'm short-time, Sergeant.
I believe in saving my money.

169
00:13:33,763 --> 00:13:37,243
Don't worry about that.
I was gonna do it for free.

170
00:13:38,498 --> 00:13:40,539
Let me put it this way.

171
00:13:40,611 --> 00:13:42,880
Maybe I'd sleep with you
if you were the last man on Earth.

172
00:13:44,514 --> 00:13:46,457
But we're not on Earth.

173
00:13:50,049 --> 00:13:52,603
It's a voltage overload,
most likely.

174
00:13:53,315 --> 00:13:55,453
You want to check it out?

175
00:13:55,522 --> 00:13:57,082
It's probably nothing.

176
00:13:58,370 --> 00:14:00,059
But on second thought--

177
00:14:42,752 --> 00:14:45,120
Police officer.
Anybody there?

178
00:15:11,135 --> 00:15:12,892
Shit!

179
00:15:29,247 --> 00:15:31,965
- This is not making me happy.
- It's time to get backup.

180
00:16:02,975 --> 00:16:06,041
Jesus Christ.
What are you doing?

181
00:16:07,326 --> 00:16:10,806
- I almost killed you.
- What's going on?

182
00:16:10,909 --> 00:16:14,391
- Rec-fac's a slaughterhouse.
- What?

183
00:16:14,495 --> 00:16:15,923
Slaughterhouse?

184
00:16:16,926 --> 00:16:21,434
That's the word Descanso used.
I didn't see it myself.

185
00:16:21,505 --> 00:16:23,161
According to what
Commander Braddock told me...

186
00:16:23,230 --> 00:16:25,685
right after we first arrived
in Shining Canyon...

187
00:16:25,758 --> 00:16:29,555
she and the two rookies headed
towards the recreation facility.

188
00:16:29,631 --> 00:16:31,518
Mel, I'll get us squared away
at the rec-fac.

189
00:16:31,582 --> 00:16:34,168
You and Sergeant Jericho
go and check in at the jail.

190
00:16:34,238 --> 00:16:36,094
Save some hot water for me.

191
00:16:58,909 --> 00:17:01,724
Descanso, sweep left.

192
00:17:02,559 --> 00:17:04,412
Bashira, stick with me.

193
00:17:20,221 --> 00:17:22,043
Officer to train,
do you read?

194
00:17:22,622 --> 00:17:26,200
The casino, barracks, dining hall,
rec center, no one alive anywhere.

195
00:17:28,828 --> 00:17:31,350
- Commander.
- What?

196
00:17:32,735 --> 00:17:36,476
- I can't reach the train.
- Well, keep trying.

197
00:17:40,348 --> 00:17:41,397
How are we doing?

198
00:17:42,685 --> 00:17:44,474
I don't know. This thing
was built to stay locked.

199
00:17:44,542 --> 00:17:46,515
And Williams
is still locked up?

200
00:17:47,868 --> 00:17:48,796
What do you mean?

201
00:17:48,861 --> 00:17:51,513
Williams was arrested
on the suspicion of murdering...

202
00:17:51,583 --> 00:17:55,258
six rail workers and a payroll courier
up at Klik 305 Hub Station.

203
00:17:55,326 --> 00:17:59,417
The bodies were hung and decapitated,
just like the bodies in the rec-fac.

204
00:18:00,829 --> 00:18:02,487
So how'd they pin that
on Desolation?

205
00:18:02,558 --> 00:18:04,182
He showed up here
with the courier's payroll.

206
00:18:04,252 --> 00:18:06,228
The cashier realized
it was a stolen scrip.

207
00:18:06,301 --> 00:18:08,210
They made the arrest.

208
00:18:08,285 --> 00:18:10,870
There's got to be a day log
here somewhere.

209
00:18:12,125 --> 00:18:13,466
Sergeant's desk.

210
00:18:22,461 --> 00:18:24,119
Here.

211
00:18:26,845 --> 00:18:29,877
Last night the mine called in
a work stoppage.

212
00:18:29,947 --> 00:18:32,337
Reported winds
gusting up to 60 knots.

213
00:18:32,413 --> 00:18:34,354
- Sixty?
- That's what it says.

214
00:18:35,004 --> 00:18:36,412
Anything else?

215
00:18:36,476 --> 00:18:39,291
Arrest for theft, then nothing.

216
00:18:41,563 --> 00:18:43,190
Got it.

217
00:19:07,899 --> 00:19:09,109
What's going on around here?

218
00:19:09,180 --> 00:19:12,792
We haven't had a meal
or a piss break in six hours.

219
00:19:12,860 --> 00:19:15,095
Descanso, open the door.

220
00:19:15,163 --> 00:19:17,367
All right, everybody, answer "here"
when I call your name.

221
00:19:17,436 --> 00:19:18,996
- Akooshay.
- What?

222
00:19:19,067 --> 00:19:20,594
Just answer "here."

223
00:19:20,669 --> 00:19:22,326
- Yeah.
- Zimmerman.

224
00:19:22,428 --> 00:19:24,283
I'm right in front of you.

225
00:19:24,348 --> 00:19:25,591
Benchley.

226
00:19:27,324 --> 00:19:30,519
- Who's that?
- She showed up last night.

227
00:19:31,451 --> 00:19:34,866
Checked herself in. Insisted on
being locked up here with us.

228
00:19:34,938 --> 00:19:36,827
Well, wake her up, sunshine.

229
00:19:36,891 --> 00:19:38,898
Let's see what she has to say.

230
00:19:42,011 --> 00:19:44,083
Somebody wants to talk to you.

231
00:19:45,115 --> 00:19:47,832
- Who are you?
- Whitlock.

232
00:19:47,899 --> 00:19:50,420
What are you doing
in the holding tank, Whitlock?

233
00:19:51,898 --> 00:19:54,387
It's the only safe place
at the moment, okay?

234
00:19:54,491 --> 00:19:56,596
- Can I go back to sleep now?
- No, you can't!

235
00:19:56,699 --> 00:19:59,829
I need answers.
What's going on out there?

236
00:20:03,034 --> 00:20:04,409
What's your I.D.?

237
00:20:06,684 --> 00:20:10,031
Dr. Arlene Whitlock.
I'm the Spec Six science officer...

238
00:20:10,106 --> 00:20:13,784
in charge of the mining operation
at Drucker's Ridge.

239
00:20:14,459 --> 00:20:18,900
I left Drucker's about a week ago
with a weather balloon I'd modified.

240
00:20:18,971 --> 00:20:24,152
There was a disturbance in town.
It seemed prudent to get out.

241
00:20:24,219 --> 00:20:27,064
They said there was a riot
and the place was destroyed.

242
00:20:27,129 --> 00:20:28,984
Yeah, something like that.

243
00:20:29,049 --> 00:20:32,084
I was adrift for several days,
you know.

244
00:20:32,155 --> 00:20:33,910
Ran out of food.

245
00:20:33,978 --> 00:20:37,274
I followed the railroad tracks
