Okay, go! Go!

752
01:13:42,716 --> 01:13:44,058
What the hell happened to you?

753
01:13:44,124 --> 01:13:46,295
We got trapped a couple of kliks
north of here, trying to off-load.

754
01:13:46,396 --> 01:13:47,640
I'll get us out of here.

755
01:14:01,693 --> 01:14:04,026
We've got to go back.

756
01:14:04,092 --> 01:14:06,994
Slow the train down outside of town,
then come to a complete stop.

757
01:14:09,019 --> 01:14:10,394
No way.

758
01:14:11,548 --> 01:14:15,257
- I'm giving you an order.
- I don't care. The answer's no.

759
01:14:18,396 --> 01:14:20,218
The answer's yes.

760
01:14:21,660 --> 01:14:23,415
Look...

761
01:14:23,483 --> 01:14:28,698
even if we get back to Chryse,
those things will just keep coming.

762
01:14:28,763 --> 01:14:30,618
We've got a chance here.

763
01:14:32,058 --> 01:14:34,742
We've got a chance to stop this thing
before it goes any further.

764
01:14:35,324 --> 01:14:37,778
This is about one thing--

765
01:14:37,851 --> 01:14:39,226
dominion.

766
01:14:40,539 --> 01:14:42,448
It's not their planet anymore.

767
01:14:43,323 --> 01:14:44,849
What about him?

768
01:14:44,922 --> 01:14:47,345
Isn't it our job
to take him back?

769
01:14:49,658 --> 01:14:52,114
Is he still a prisoner
or is he one of us?

770
01:14:53,787 --> 01:14:56,404
I can give a damn
about saving this planet.

771
01:14:57,466 --> 01:15:00,532
Seems like it's been after me
since the day I was born.

772
01:15:02,330 --> 01:15:05,014
If I'm gonna die,
I'm gonna die fighting...

773
01:15:05,083 --> 01:15:06,840
not running.

774
01:15:20,090 --> 01:15:23,090
If we blew up the nuclear
power station, what would happen?

775
01:15:23,194 --> 01:15:25,168
I mean, there'd be
a huge explosion, right?

776
01:15:25,274 --> 01:15:28,373
No, not unless you retract
the control rods and expose the core.

777
01:15:28,442 --> 01:15:29,815
Then what?

778
01:15:31,258 --> 01:15:34,553
Then you'd have a small
atomic bomb going "boom."

779
01:15:36,570 --> 01:15:37,464
How small?

780
01:15:39,129 --> 01:15:42,262
I don't know. It'd blow out
a radius of a mile, maybe two.

781
01:15:46,617 --> 01:15:47,960
Would it kill them?

782
01:15:48,026 --> 01:15:50,393
It would certainly destroy
their human hosts, but as for them...

783
01:15:51,641 --> 01:15:52,754
I don't know.

784
01:15:56,473 --> 01:15:58,613
Jericho, can you get us in?

785
01:16:00,282 --> 01:16:01,654
I can try.

786
01:16:17,049 --> 01:16:18,839
The plan was simple.

787
01:16:18,906 --> 01:16:21,622
Sergeant Jericho, the science officer
and I jumped off the train...

788
01:16:21,689 --> 01:16:23,829
and headed towards
the powerplant.

789
01:16:23,898 --> 01:16:27,410
The others stayed aboard the train
as it backed into the station.

790
01:16:27,513 --> 01:16:29,335
The idea was they provide cover...

791
01:16:29,401 --> 01:16:32,946
and distract the Martians
as we set the charges in the plant.

792
01:16:33,016 --> 01:16:35,057
And they'd swing back, pick us up
and we'd all get as far away...

793
01:16:35,130 --> 01:16:37,267
from Shining Canyon as we could
before the place blew.

794
01:16:37,337 --> 01:16:39,704
Like I said,
it was a simple plan.

795
01:16:40,729 --> 01:16:43,249
The only problem was, it didn't work
the way it was supposed to.

796
01:16:50,937 --> 01:16:53,392
- How are you doing,Jericho?
- I'm working on it.

797
01:16:53,465 --> 01:16:54,578
Hurry up.

798
01:17:09,239 --> 01:17:12,851
We've got to remove the waterjacket
and destroy the containment shell.

799
01:17:12,920 --> 01:17:14,382
Where do I put the dynamite?

800
01:17:29,945 --> 01:17:33,589
Officer to the train, they've
spotted us. Get your ass back here now.

801
01:18:35,287 --> 01:18:36,268
Yeah?

802
01:19:16,277 --> 01:19:17,652
Let's go.

803
01:20:03,093 --> 01:20:04,466
We've got to get out
of here fast.

804
01:20:04,533 --> 01:20:06,986
The Doc says the blast radius
could be up to two miles.

805
01:20:07,060 --> 01:20:09,232
- What does that mean?
- It means step on it.

806
01:20:30,004 --> 01:20:31,859
Stay here and keep it
full throttle.

807
01:20:31,923 --> 01:20:33,234
What are you gonna do?

808
01:20:33,301 --> 01:20:34,990
Lighten our load.

809
01:20:37,620 --> 01:20:40,008
I think there's some
more dynamite in the rear car.

810
01:22:58,353 --> 01:23:00,525
See you later,
you big motherfucker.

811
01:23:29,808 --> 01:23:30,921
You okay?

812
01:23:31,697 --> 01:23:32,591
Say your prayers.

813
01:24:06,352 --> 01:24:09,069
I didn't know
you was cut this deep.

814
01:24:10,191 --> 01:24:13,258
Should've taken care
of this hours ago.

815
01:24:13,904 --> 01:24:16,269
You do that like a pro.

816
01:24:16,336 --> 01:24:17,644
Yeah.

817
01:24:17,711 --> 01:24:20,101
Me and my brother
been through a lot of battles...

818
01:24:21,327 --> 01:24:23,269
ever since we was kids.

819
01:24:26,544 --> 01:24:29,259
I never thought I'd go to war
with somebody like you.

820
01:24:30,640 --> 01:24:34,184
I know when you get to Chryse, you'll
tell those people that I helped you...

821
01:24:35,215 --> 01:24:37,802
and I wasn't the cause
of all this mess around here.

822
01:24:38,929 --> 01:24:41,863
'Cause I know they're looking
for somebody to blame.

823
01:24:41,936 --> 01:24:44,357
I swear to you, Williams...

824
01:24:44,431 --> 01:24:48,260
as soon as I get back, I'm gonna tell my
superiors about this fucked-up planet.

825
01:24:49,360 --> 01:24:51,977
They'll drop the charges
as soon as they get the report.

826
01:24:59,055 --> 01:25:00,943
That ought to hold it.

827
01:25:01,039 --> 01:25:03,046
When you get there,
have somebody look at it.

828
01:25:04,110 --> 01:25:07,494
I couldn't get it perfect,
so it might leave a scar.

829
01:25:07,567 --> 01:25:08,843
I'm getting a collection.

830
01:25:08,911 --> 01:25:10,918
You'll be all right.

831
01:25:14,223 --> 01:25:16,077
- Comfortable?
- Yeah.

832
01:25:17,647 --> 01:25:19,501
I'll get you a blanket.

833
01:25:30,223 --> 01:25:32,165
What the hell are you doing?

834
01:25:32,814 --> 01:25:34,669
Oh, this is where I get off.

835
01:25:34,734 --> 01:25:36,807
What are you talking about?

836
01:25:36,877 --> 01:25:40,652
We'll be in Chryse soon.
Can't let you turn me in.

837
01:25:42,542 --> 01:25:44,397
I can't let you walk.

838
01:25:48,845 --> 01:25:51,562
What you gonna do,
fucking shoot me?

839
01:25:59,533 --> 01:26:00,843
There's nowhere to run.

840
01:26:04,077 --> 01:26:06,085
Anywhere is better than hell.

841
01:26:09,006 --> 01:26:10,860
Catch you later.

842
01:26:14,126 --> 01:26:15,980
Yeah, right.

843
01:26:22,925 --> 01:26:24,300
Shit.

844
01:26:31,694 --> 01:26:33,896
And what happened to Williams?

845
01:26:33,998 --> 01:26:35,404
I don't know.

846
01:26:35,470 --> 01:26:37,292
When I woke up, he was gone.

847
01:26:37,357 --> 01:26:38,600
And you were handcuffed?

848
01:26:39,724 --> 01:26:41,580
Must've done it
while I slept.

849
01:26:42,605 --> 01:26:44,460
At that point,
I trusted him.

850
01:26:46,348 --> 01:26:48,323
That's all you have to tell us?

851
01:26:49,133 --> 01:26:50,987
That's all I know.

852
01:26:52,204 --> 01:26:55,653
All right, Lieutenant Ballard,
I suggest you get some rest.

853
01:26:55,726 --> 01:26:57,580
You're dismissed.

854
01:27:09,900 --> 01:27:14,372
Is our statement to the Cartel going to
be that Mars is being overrun by ghosts?

855
01:27:38,668 --> 01:27:40,556
Attention, all police personnel...

856
01:27:40,652 --> 01:27:42,888
report to your nearest
munitions station immediately...

857
01:27:42,956 --> 01:27:44,614
for weaponry assignment.

858
01:27:44,684 --> 01:27:47,586
A security breach has occurred
in the south quadrant.

859
01:27:47,659 --> 01:27:50,561
This is a level-ten emergency.

860
01:27:50,635 --> 01:27:55,208
All police personnel, report to your
division sergeant for assignment.

861
01:27:55,276 --> 01:27:58,593
All civilian personnel,
evacuate the streets immediately.

862
01:27:58,668 --> 01:28:01,319
Please remain indoors
until further instructed.

863
01:28:14,795 --> 01:28:15,689
Come on.

864
01:28:17,644 --> 01:28:20,708
Tide is up.
Time to stay alive.

865
01:28:31,946 --> 01:28:35,743
If you ever wanna come to the other
side, you'd make a hell of a crook.

866
01:28:35,819 --> 01:28:37,673
You'd make a hell of a cop.

867
01:28:40,235 --> 01:28:41,696
Let's just kick some ass.

